<br>
I really can't think of a valid reason why we go anon in RvR - other realms can only see what members of their realm are in a zone and thus it doesn't seem to make much difference, but is something that people are always saying we should do, so we have been doing it. But like you, I'm not really sure why.<br>
<br>
I do agree with Belce on this one though and it is something we have discussed before.  Basically, I don't think letting people pick their own groups is a good method to go about organizing balanced groups. By letting people pick their own groups, I think we will find that the first group selected will almost always have the most balanced and highest level mix.<br>
<br>
Think of when you played team sports on the play ground at school.  If you let one team pick before the other team even was able to select any of it's members, the first team would most definitly be stronger.<br>
<br>
Thus I think the task should fall to either the Battle Commander or the Raid Leader and I'm leaning towards the Battle Command at this time only because I think the Raid Leader will be busy dealing with the set-up of the chat channel and late arrivals. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/ucreirwyy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Creirwyy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BEEP BEEP (poor pedestrian)</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/3/02 10:07:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://werzat.freeservers.com/d_photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR on January 1st, 2002</span><hr size=1> I suggest attendance is taken by Raid Commander only.  Raid commander sets up one person outside of Battle Commander and themselves to set up chat channel.<br>
<br>
Raid Commander advises chat channel person who the Group Leaders are to be and gets them invited immediately.  Groups are announced in the chat channel and the Group Leaders go about getting their own groups set up.  Group Leaders advice chat channel person who is their back up GL and advises chat channel person.<br>
<br>
Also I have found the other nite this helped.  Not only all Stealth class are in chat channel, but all minstrels should be as well.  The minstrels should be /stuck on the Battle Commander and the rest of their group should be /stuck on the minstrel.  Minstrels move quickly.<br>
<br>
When a move is called, we did this the other nite and it worked somewhat better.  Battle Commander says<br>
&quot;moving in 3&quot;<br>
&quot;2&quot;<br>
&quot;1 MOVE&quot;    <br>
You can make up simple hotkeys for these.  That helps alleviate some of the lag/delay problems.<br>
<br>
When assigning groups, we continue with G1, G2, G3, etc. but now with a twist.<br>
Each group has their own MA.  G1 is responsible for pushing thru to the back, to get the healers; G2 goes after the casters in the middle and G3 and whatever go after the tanks.<br>
This way you could actually make up groups that are efficient to take out certain classes/races.  <br>
(i.e.)  G1 has the fastest Minstrel so they can get to the back and mez the healers, the sorcerer would be great in this group as well for the AoE mez, which ever.  G3 could be made up of mostly tank types to smack down the other tanks.<br>
This is just a concept of mine in the making, I need to work on it a bit more, and collect some more data.<br>
<br>
Your ever quiet minstrel &lt;Belce replaces the Duck Tape on her mouth once again&gt;.<br>
