<br>
As you are almost always in the scout team I think you may not be aware of the problems we have been having with group balance when letting GL's pick their groups.<br>
<br>
I for one have never seen a raid where people are not talking about group balance after the fact.  I remember the last raid I was in, I was in a group with 3 casters and 1 tank.  The problem was that while I was level 35 cleric, the other players were all below level 20 except for our group leader who was level 29 and a caster. Group 1 had 2 additional members and had a mix of 3 tanks and 3 casters.  Every person in group one was with-in 1 to 2 levels of each other and thus by allowing them to have an extremely well balanced group, the other two groups where seriously comprimised.<br>
<br>
The raid before, while I was in a balanced group (I was in the first group selected) I clearly remember others complaining that their group make-up was seriously lacking.<br>
<br>
It seems that once again in the last raid, that we are still having trouble with groupings and I think we need to address this problem and it should be the first thing on our agenda. I think no one will take us seriously if the join the raid only to find that they are in a gimped group while another group is a power house.  I also think that we could do every thing else right and still be defeated only because we have poor group balance.<br>
<br>
I think we need to come up with a way to ensure that we are putting together solid balanced groups that can accomplish the tasks we are assigning them.  We need to mix in the lower level players equally in our groups or assign them more of a support role.  We need to ensure that we have equal distrubution of tanks and casters or what ever mix of players we are looking for should we have speicific group tactics.<br>
<br>
I think the only way we can accomplish this is to have one person organize the groups.  This person should understand the tactics we will be using both in group and large formations and must understand the objectives we have set for the raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/ucreirwyy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Creirwyy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BEEP BEEP (poor pedestrian)</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/3/02 10:47:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://werzat.freeservers.com/d_photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR on January 1st, 2002</span><hr size=1> Wasn't that exactly my suggestion?<br>
