<br>
Sorry Dulcette, I misunderstood your post when I saw &quot;Group Leaders go about getting their own groups set up&quot;.<br>
<br>
That being said, Dulcette, Belce, Lorne and I used to meet to hold discussions about RvR and the directions we wanted to take it. Since that time, Haemish, Belce, Lorne and I have met and laid the ground work for what I thought was a very sound idea.<br>
<br>
Basically each guild would hold meetings internally to discuss RvR tactics and things of this nature.  From there 2 members from each guild would meet to bring these ideas forward.  The idea is that should Seekers and Daggers enter into an alliance, in time we would probably have more guilds in the alliance and it would be benificial to take this approach from the beginning.<br>
<br>
Haemish and I had a quick conversation before the holidays and I informed him that I would not be available over the holidays and that we would probably be best off to set up our next meeting for after the holidays.<br>
<br>
I think every one knows that I am always open to getting together to discuss ideas and hear peoples opinions, I just think we need some structure to these meetings.<br>
<br>
That being said, the Seekers have organized a council to discuss RvR ideas internally in our own guild.  We held our first meeting just before the holidays and I think we had a lot of good ideas.  We will be holding our next meeting next week and I look foward to getting together with Dagger representatives to discuss the ideas further.<br>
<br>
Just a quick note on moving foward vs moving backwards.  I honestly don't think one bad night can be enough to say that things are moving backwards.  Let's take last night for example.<br>
<br>
We had a small single party group going out on a raid.  I can honestly say that I have run more organized and effective single group raids with non-Seekers/Dagger people.  Yes we had trouble at first with people paying attention and yes IT IS FRUSTRATING (takes a breath) from time to time when this happens.<br>
<br>
However, in time people did start paying attention and we did have better success.  However, one of the main problems we did have is that our scout (while he did do a bang up job) is very new to RvR.  I had trouble giving directions to him and when I thought he was in the second southern valley, he was in fact in the first southern valley. But hell that is what this game is all about and I don't see it as a step backwards.<br>
<br>
As I have said, I was away for about 2 weeks (I don't get many chances to spend time with my sister) and have not been nearly as involved as I normally am or would have liked to have been.  However, the holidays are over, I am back to my normal routine.  I guarantee you that I will be the first one there to discuss/aid/assist in any thing that will be done in a constructive manner. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/umolfious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Molfious</A> at: 1/3/02 3:31:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/ucreirwyy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Creirwyy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BEEP BEEP (poor pedestrian)</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/3/02 3:23:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://werzat.freeservers.com/d_photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR on January 1st, 2002</span><hr size=1> - I agree that there should be a RvR tactical team.  And it would be nice to see one in the Daggers.<br>
