- When sending out scouts they move really really really slow.  Might be a good idea on any given day for Battle Commander/Raid Commander of the future to go spend some one on one time with a Stealth player and count off how long it takes them to get from point a to point b.  Too many times a call is moved beyond where the stealth player &lt;s&gt; are.<br>
<br>
- It was not one night, it was two nite's in a row.  And the most frustrating part was we are eight really good players and we weren't listening, we weren't stuck together, we were moving without calls being made, we got RVR realm point happy without consideration for the group, and the list goes on.  If we, the eight who were their last nite can't get our acts together to run as an efficient team how can we possibly ever expect of the others around us.  How can we possibly lead by example?  When myself and one other member were all by ourselves last nite at MF1, we actually shrugged together.  Yes two very experienced RvR players were completely lost as to what was going on and didn't gain one realm point due to it.  So yes that is very frustrating.<br>
<br>
- I think the meetings were a good thing.  We were holding them on a consistent basis and I would hope that know that the holidays are over that will happen again immediately.<br>
<br>
- regarding the attached quote from Molfious, could we hear what that ground work is?<br>
&quot;Since that time, Haemish, Belce, Lorne and I have met and laid the ground work for what I thought was a very sound idea.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
