</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/umolfious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Molfious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/3/02 9:41:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://seekersoflore.com/daoc/members/molfious.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR on January 1st, 2002</span><hr size=1> Let me clarify here a bit.  It is my intent to hold regular meetings to discuss the many things that an alliance would require us to invest time and engery into.<br>
<br>
One of these topics would be RvR and the ways we can make it better.<br>
<br>
The key here is as has been stated by every one already, is to develop a standard set of protocals if you will that govern the ways in which we conduct RvR.<br>
<br>
I played EQ on a regular server for 2 years and I can tell you that after a year on a PvP server that large scale raids against mobs are much different than large scale raids against other players.  I also played another team game for a long time in the PGL and I can tell that team dynamics when you are competing against other players are much different than when you are playing against a static mob.  I do not claim to have the answers and/or the knowledge that some how makes me better than any one else at this sort of thing, but I do hold a firm belief in the fact that through organization and a whole lot of grouping and practice that we will learn in time to not only anticipate each others actions but work as a very cohesive unit.  <br>
<br>
In the other game I speak of that we played in the professional gaming league, we needed the ability to communicate and communicate quickly.  We also had to understand each others style of play and learn to use our strengths to the best of our abilities to maximize our effectiveness.  We also had to learn how the opposing teams worked and what types of strategies they would use against us.  We spent a great deal of time working in small groups getting know each other and played the game over and over again not only against opposing teams, but against each other.  We developed a short hand and had specific keyboard mappings to communicate quickly and conscisely. We understood all the maps forwards and backwards and could navigate them in total darkness as if it was second nature.<br>
But again these things take time and commitment, something I feel I have not offered enough of at this point and time. But I would like to change this now, so here is what I suggest.<br>
<br>
I hear by announce that for the course of my stay in DAoC that I am committed to developing the same degree of unity between our two guilds.  I would like to see our guilds rise to this challenge and become the best that we can be in all areas related to playing the game including RvR and PvE.<br>
<br>
Therefore I would like to extend an invite to Haemish and all the Silver Daggers to step forth and join me in developing strategy, tactics and communication.  It will not be easy, it will not happen over night.  But as has been so wisely stated by Dulcette and many others, we have covered many of these things already and we need not move backwards, but rather we should be moving forward.<br>
<br>
Therefore I would like to merge our council of tactics with a division with-in the Silver Daggers, our goal to develop tactics, strategy and communication methods that will unite us into a cohesive unit prepared to take on the challenges that we will face in the coming months and years in DAoC.<br>
<br>
I would like to have regular meetings between the groups and work on quickly developing short hand communication, orders of movement, scouting tactics, battle divisions, group formations and seige tactics.  The key will be playing the game together as much as possible both PvE and RvR.<br>
<br>
As I have said, I am committed 100% to this and will do every thing I can to help bring about the things I have mentioned. But with out you all, I will surely fail and failure is something I do not take lightly.<br>
<br>
I will be speaking with Haemish more in game ASAP to see if this is something he believes your guild desires. But if the members of the Silver Daggers I already call friend are any indication I see no reason why this endevor should not move forward. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/umolfious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Molfious</A> at: 1/4/02 12:19:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/bdaggersincamelot.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belce>Belce</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.macaulay.org/macabdge.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(1/4/02 12:37:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.macaulay.org/macabdge.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RvR on January 1st, 2002</span><hr size=1> The main reason why I want our guild to be in alliance with the Seekers is in the post above.   <p>Belce Gaegwyn<BR>
